      <title>Hardware-Aware Transformers for Long Sequence Modeling</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/hardware_aware_transformers/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 15 Mar 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>mycaptainmy@gmail.com (Yuan Meng)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/hardware_aware_transformers/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;graphics-processing-units-gpus-how-game-cards-are-born-for-deep-learning&#34; class=&#34;scroll-mt-8 group&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Graphics Processing Units (GPUs): How Game Cards Are Born for Deep Learning&#xA;  &#xA;    &lt;a href=&#34;#graphics-processing-units-gpus-how-game-cards-are-born-for-deep-learning&#34;&#xA;        class=&#34;no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block&#34;&#xA;        aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to this heading&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg&#xA;  xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&#xA;  width=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  height=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  fill=&#34;none&#34;&#xA;  stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&#xA;  class=&#34;lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block&#34;&#xA;  viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Inside your Nintendo Switch are graphics processing units (GPUs) that render life-like scenes in real time. After the &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Game_engine&#34;&gt;game engine&lt;/a&gt; determines how characters act and what objects look like based on rules and physics, GPUs break down the scene into small units (e.g., triangles and vertices) and render pixels, lighting, textures, and other graph elements in each simultaneously. Without this parallelism, the game world will unfold slowly, making any game stuck and unplayable.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/oirp77bh00gkux8gtic5v/Screenshot-2025-03-15-at-2.58.36-PM.png?rlkey=qstiht7lzgzbvpm4wgqzhkt18&amp;amp;st=g3s1ufu5&amp;amp;raw=1&#34;&#xA;    alt=&#34;Game graphics are rendered seamlessly by graphics processing units (GPUs) thanks to their massive parallel processing power.&#34; width=&#34;500&#34;&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;&#xA;      &lt;p&gt;Game graphics are rendered seamlessly by graphics processing units (GPUs) thanks to their massive parallel processing power.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Turns out matrix multiplications &amp;mdash; the building blocks of modern deep learning &amp;mdash; can similarly be broken into many small units and get processed in parallel, the very task that GPUs are born for.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
